msContents.summary: Contains a selection of 55 chapters from the Qur'ān with other prayers.

supportDesc.extent: 172 leaves : 113 x 67 (73 x 36) mm, bound to 115 x 72 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Modern foliation added in pencil, upper left recto; catchwords every verso, lower left.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in naskh in black ink; some elements in nastaʻliq; pointed, partially vocalized.

decoDesc.decoNote: Dual-page illuminated first opening with polychrome and gold headpiece, gold floral margin fill and text on cloudbands (f. 1v-[2]r). All other pages are ruled in between each line in gold and black and border-ruled in gold, black, red. Gold roundels mark verse endings. Rubrications in red, including headers and readings.

binding.p: Lacquer cover with red central floral medallion with painted flower in-fill and two matching pendants along the vertical axis on an orange background with an inscribed frame in off white on a red background. Bright orange paper doublure.

origin.p: Item is not dated, but likely copied in Iran in the 18th century or first half of the 19th century.
